text: The seductive power of depression Depression is seductive  it offends and teases  frightens you and draws you in  tempting you with its promise of sweet oblivion  then overwhelming you with a nearly sexual power  squirming past your defenses  dissolving your will  invading the tired spirit so utterly that it becomes difficult to recall that you ever lived without it or to imagine that you might live that way again  With all the guile of Satan himself  depression persuades you that its invasion was all your own idea  that you wanted it all along  It fogs the part of the brain that reasons  that knows right and wrong  It captures you with its warm  guilty  hateful pleasures  and  worst of all  it becomes familiar  All at once  you find yourself in thrall to the very thing that most terrifies you  Your work slides  your friendships slide  your marriage slides  but you scarcely notice  to be depressed is to be half in love with disaster    Stephen L  Carter Yesterday I posted about how my anti depressants  after   months and several dosage increases  are finally working  They ve restored some  definitely not all  of my energy and I m remembering the feeling of pleasure and excitement I used to have years ago  All of a sudden I enjoy music again  my thoughts a filled with ideas of how to love the people in my life and I can laugh on my own accord   I had grown so comfortable with being a recluse  drinking the pain away  being a flake and indulging in alone time  LOTS of alone time  I thought that s what I needed  and perhaps that s still true  But I had grown comfortable with constant unhappiness because to feel anything warm  I had to fight against every lie of depression  Who has the energy for that  Certainly no one who suffers from anxiety and depression  This medication has restored an energy that I thought I d never get back and it feels so much better than the comfort I found in reclusion  I d just forgotten  or lost hope of anything better   I still feel something pulling me towards the lifestyle I had when my depression was at its peak but right now in this moment I feel good  and that is triumphant
summary: Stephen L Carter's anti-depressants are working and he's feeling better. He used to be depressed, but now he's remembering the feeling of pleasure and excitement he used to have years ago. He's enjoying music again and he can laugh on his own accord.
cleaned: stephen carter anti depressant work feel well depress remember feeling pleasure excitement year ago enjoy music laugh accord
